{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c4c5c292-82b4-4886-b219-faad6ec5ef72","content":"Here are the MSBuild evaluation performance issues I found:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Recursive Wildcard Glob (EvalHeavy.csproj, line 9)\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\n`**\\*.*` forces MSBuild to **walk the entire directory tree** during evaluation. This is the most expensive pattern here — it scales with the number of files on disk. Narrow it to specific extensions (e.g., `**\\*.txt`) or remove it if not needed.\n\n### 2. File I/O via Property Function (EvalHeavy.csproj, line 13)\n```xml\n<BuildNotes …>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nCalling `System.IO.File.ReadAllText` **during evaluation** is costly. Property functions that perform I/O block the evaluator. Prefer reading file contents at build time via a `Target` with `ReadLinesFromFile`, or use an `Exec` task instead.\n\n### 3. Chained Import Depth (level1 → level2 → level3)\n```\nEvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nA **3-level deep import chain** where each file does nothing but set one property and import the next. Every import adds XML parse + evaluate overhead. Flatten these into a single `.props` file to reduce import resolution passes.\n\n### 4. Import Outside SDK Ordering (line 6)\nThe `<Import>` of `level1.props` sits between the SDK implicit imports, which is fine syntactically but means MSBuild must resolve the chained imports **mid-evaluation**. Moving custom properties into `Directory.Build.props` lets the SDK handle ordering more efficiently.\n\n---\n\n**Summary of impact (highest → lowest):**\n\n| Issue | Impact |\n|---|---|\n| `**\\*.*` recursive glob | 🔴 High — scales with filesystem |\n| `File::ReadAllText` in evaluation | 🔴 High — synchronous I/O blocks evaluator |\n| 3-level import chain | 🟡 Medium — extra parse passes |\n| Import placement | 🟢 Low — minor ordering overhead |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0dc43efb-423e-4a6f-8ada-5100bc6cff4e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a complete picture of the project. Let me analyze the MSBuild evaluation performance issues:\n\n1. **Recursive wildcard glob** (`**\\*.*`) in AdditionalFiles - this causes MSBuild to walk the entire directory tree during evaluation\n2. **File I/O during evaluation** - `$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))` reads a file during property evaluation, which is expensive\n3. **Deep import chain** - level1.props → level2.props → level3.props creates a 3-level deep import chain that increases evaluation time\n4. **Overly broad glob** - The `**\\*.*` pattern matches everything, not just specific file types\n\n\n5. **Unnecessary property reads** - Reading files at evaluation time blocks the entire build process","outputTokens":739,"requestId":"0405:14FF5F:5F77CB7:68512B3:69F00FFD"},"id":"556830ab-2282-4274-8df6-edf0e4c22866","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:40:32.584Z","parentId":"0e6e520e-9d02-4edd-b203-e7662b6de7a0"}
